-- Brazil Central Bank Widens Goal Beyond Inflation, Economico Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2012-05-08T19:15:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/brazil-central-bank-widens-goal-beyond-inflation-economico-says.html
Brazil ’s central bank is no longer
pursuing inflation control as its ultimate goal, Industry
Minister Fernando Pimentel told Brasil Economico.  While price stability remains a necessity, the government’s
final objective is economic growth, job creation and social
well-being, Pimentel said, according to the Sao Paulo-based
newspaper today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Raymond Colitt in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 rcolitt@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 